Acting Gauteng Health MEC, Jacob Mamabolo, has met unions and managers at health care facilities in the province. Let's speak to MEC Mamabolo to find out how he plans to deal with these concerns. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Acting Gauteng Health MEC Jacob Mamabolo says he has found substandard protective gear in some warehouses. He met unions and managers at health care facilities in the province. Some health workers say because they are not working in COVID-19 wards, they are not given proper equipment. READ: Jacob Mamabolo appointed acting-Gauteng Health MEC They claim the department is putting their lives at risk. "There is a challenge with PPE, relating to quality as you said and that has a direct bearing on the rate of infections," he said. Mamabolo says his department is looking into the matter. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.